    <div class="wrapper">
      <header>
        <% include ../partials/navbar %>
        <h3>About Express</h3>
      </header>
      <main class="container">
        <section>
          <h4> <a href="#introduction" class="link">#</a> Introduction</h4>
          <article id="introduction">
            <p>This is an example application to teach how to use node, express, mongoDB, mongoose and ejs.In this application
              Creating, Reading, Updating and Deleting (CRUD) operatons are implemented. By building this application, students will
              learn:</p>
            <ul class="ul-list">
              <li class="list">How to route using different request methods</li>
              <li class="list">How to use different middlewares</li>
              <li class="list">How to serve static files</li>
              <li class="list">How to create mongoose schema</li>
              <li class="list">How to store data in mongoDB</li>
              <li class="list">How to render data to ui using ejs a templating engine</li>
            </ul>

          </article>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4><a href="#about-express" class="link">#</a> Express</h4>
          <article id="about-express">
            <p>
              Express is a minimal and flexible Node.js web application framework that provides a robust set of features for web and
              mobile applications.
            </p>

          </article>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h4> <a href="#packages" class="link">#</a> Necessary pacakges to build this application:</h4>
          <article id="packages">
            <pre> $ yarn add express</pre>
            <pre> $ yarn add body-parser</pre>
            <pre> $ yarn add mongoose </pre>
            <pre> $ yarn add ejs </pre>
            <pre> $ yarn add dotenv </pre>
        
          </article>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h4> <a href="#express-website" class="link">#</a> Check out the official website to learn more about Express:</h4>
